The function defined by
\[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
x + k & \text{if $x < 4$}, \\
2x - 3 & \text{if $x \ge 4$}
\end{array}
\right.\]has an inverse, and the inverse is defined for all real numbers.  Enter all possible values of $k,$ separated by commas. ||| To find the value of $k$ for which the function has an inverse, we check the continuity at $x = 4$. Since $f(4) = 5$, if we set $k$ to be 5, we have the equation $x + k = 5$ which gives $k = 0$. Therefore, the possible value for $k$ is $0$.

summary:
Note that $f(4) = 5.$  If we set $k$ so that $x + 4 = 5,$ then $k = 1.$  This value of $k$ makes the function continuous, as shown below.

