Multiplying the equation $f(x) = \frac1{x+1} + \frac1x + \frac1{x-1} = 1$ by $(x+1)x(x-1)$ and then rearranging, we get the cubic equation \[x^3 - 3x^2 - x + 1 = 0.\]By Vieta's formulas, the sum of the roots of this equation is $\boxed{3}.$

Note using the change-of-base formula that $\log_y x \log_x y = 1$. We find that \begin{align*}
(\log_y x)^2 + (\log_x y)^2 &= (\log_y x)^2 + 2\log_y x \log_x y + (\log_x y)^2 - 2\log_y x \log_x y \\
&= (\log_y x + \log_x y)^2 - 2\log_y x \log_x y \\
&= 7^2 - 2 \\
&= \boxed{47}.
\end{align*}

